going on. What has this done to the climate in your 
department as far as teacher morale or anxiety or

02:11.532 --> 02:19.642
the unknown? The fear of the unknown, I guess, is 
the worst. How do you deal with that as a department

02:23.406 --> 02:26.349
head and manager? How do you manage the people? 
Well, that's part of the management problem. I

02:32.637 --> 02:38.203
think that if you're perceived as trying to 
maintain a class load that is appropriate. For

02:41.873 --> 03:00.204
example, the time I spend with these kids who need 
to get into classes, I do not add a student to a class

02:41.873 --> 03:00.204
except in an emergency, unless a faculty member 
has signed a form accepting the student. Now let me

03:00.224 --> 03:01.005
explain that. If you came to me and you said you 
wanted to get into a class and it was closed I would

03:04.390 --> 03:31.360
say here is a form and you need to take this to 
Professor Alexander and her class is closed and if

03:04.390 --> 03:31.360
she signs her name on this accepting you into that 
class then I will admit you so Pat Alexander has

03:04.390 --> 03:31.360
made the decision that she will take that 31st 
student into her class then I put that person in now

03:04.390 --> 03:31.360
for those faculty who are too soft-hearted, I 
sometimes have to stop and say, you know, even the

03:32.150 --> 03:38.378
form isn't going to do. We simply can't. The 
instruction is going to be affected. So that I

03:41.743 --> 03:48.772
think in that way, the faculty understands that 
I'm just not sitting here and adding 47 kids to your

03:41.743 --> 03:48.772
class. It's their decision first. And if there's 
an emergency, then I may call and say, Pat, we have a

03:50.655 --> 03:57.825
student who's doing student teaching next 
semester. Yours is the only class. Is there any

03:59.507 --> 04:01.009
possibility we can get her in? And so I might do a 
face-to-face or a telephone conversation with a

04:01.563 --> 04:05.388
faculty member. Then that kind of leads me into all 
these changes and all the things that are

04:06.209 --> 04:17.845
happening are going to impact, obviously, the 
future and what the College of Education will be in

04:06.209 --> 04:17.845
the 21st century. And I see that you had some notes 
in there. Do you have a crystal ball to what you feel

04:19.948 --> 04:24.354
like? I think we've covered most of these. But let 
me share with you, first of all, One of the changes

04:32.596 --> 04:45.588
that I feel very positive about in regard to the 
institution,

04:32.596 --> 04:45.588
and that is the special effort that is being made 
for the recruitment of minorities. And I'm very,

04:47.891 --> 04:58.941
I'm going to be very point about that, I'm very 
proud of the fact that we now have in place an

05:00.524 --> 05:03.908
English as a second language teacher preparation 
program.

